[This disease does not seem to be letting up. Animal owners need to be especially vigilant of the fruit bats, where they roost, where fruit is that they like to eat, and keep their animals away from that area.

We are sorry for the loss of any animal life, but I know many people are keenly watching the re-testing of the dog.

The government has authorized additional dollars for more research into this disease. While it is appropriate and welcome news, it may not ease the pain of loss these people are feeling. I am sure this year will see another desire to have a vaccine sooner rather than later, and it is making progress.

Queensland, Australia may be found on the interactive HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at http://healthmap.org/r/1kJr. - Mod.TG]
